    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "Java uses the JAVA_HOME environment variable to figure out where all its component bits are. It may be that Netbeans, with the <code>--jdkhome</code> flag, has that all sorted out (I&#39;m no Netbeans expert); however I find things generally work better with JAVA_HOME properly set. So set the variable (Windows Control Panel &gt; System &gt; Advanced &gt; Environment Variables); the result of <code>echo %JAVA_HOME%</code> should print out <code>C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.8.0_131</code>"
  }, {
